.nh
.TH schedctl-run 1

.SH NAME
schedctl-run \- Run a specific scheduler


.SH SYNOPSIS
schedctl-run

.EX
[--attach|-a]
[--driver|-d]=[value]
.EE


.SH DESCRIPTION
Run a specific scheduler with optional arguments.

.PP
Arguments after -- are passed to the scheduler container.

.PP
Examples:
  schedctl run scx_rusty
  schedctl run scx_rusty -- --verbose
  schedctl run --attach scx_rusty -- --mode=performance --interval=100

.PP
\fBUsage\fP:

.EX
schedctl run SCHEDULER [-- ARGS...]
.EE


.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
\fB--attach, -a\fP: attach to the current process instead of detaching

.PP
\fB--driver, -d\fP="": container runtime to use: containerd, podman (default: "podman")
